i'm having a nightmare with an embedded project for a car ECU. it's C++ and we have this slow memory leak that only shows up after like 4 or 5 hours of steady state operation. i can't find where the allocation isn't being freed. 

here is the main telemetry loop:

void process_sensor_data(SensorPacket* packet) {
    if (packet->status == VALID) {
        DataLog* log = new DataLog(packet->payload);
        log_store->push_back(log);

        if (log_store->size() > MAX_LOG_SIZE) {
            // we should be cleaning up here but i can't track it down
            log_store->remove_oldest(); 
        }
    }
}

can you help me figure out a systematic way to track down exactly where this leak is happening? i can't use heavy tools like Valgrind because of the hardware constraints.

